{"lemma":"واد","slug":"واد","root":"#.د.#","root_slug":"_-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"واد","root":"ودي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41532","n41535","n41793","n44518"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"valley","examples":[{"text":"أَنزَلَ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ مَاءً فَسَالَتْ أَوْدِيَةٌ بِقَدَرِهَا فَاحْتَمَلَ السَّيْلُ زَبَدًا رَّابِيًا […]","english":"He has sent down water from the sky so the valleys flow, [each valley] according to its measure, so then the torrent bears a rising foam […]"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"river bed, ravine, gorge, wadi"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to engage in fellowship with, to try or strive to be friends with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be with affection for, to love"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of وَدَّ (wadda)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of وَدَى (wadā, “to whip out for discharge”)."},"ipa":["/waː.din/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41532","headword_ar":"وَاَدَ","root":"wA^d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yay^idu","text_ar":"يَيِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA^odN","text_ar":"وَاْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, L, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He buried"},{"kind":"text","text":"his daughter"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alive"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the grave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and put a load of earth upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"her. (A.) It was customary for a man in the time of paganism, when a daughter was born to him, to bury her alive when her mother brought her forth, from fear of reproach and want: but this is forbidden in the Kur. xvii. 33: and some of them used to bury their children alive in times of famine: (L:) the tribe of Kindeh used to bury their daughters alive. (S, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaA^odu AlxafiY~u","text_ar":"الوَاْدُ الخَفِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"a term used in a trad. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Extractio penis tempore concubitus, ne conciperet femina:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~ugoraY","text_ar":"الصُّغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawow^uwdapu","text_ar":"المَوْوُودَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"because this act resembles that of burying a child alive, and is done with the same motive. (L.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2914}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n41535","headword_ar":"واْدٌ","root":"wA^d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"way^iydN","text_ar":"وَيِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) absolutely: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a loud sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;) as that of a wall falling, and the like. (L.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound occasioned by vehement"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy treading"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the ground: the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the feet of camels. (L.) ―         -b3-  Also the former, (L,) or both, (K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"braying"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hadiyr","text_ar":"هَدِير"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a camel. (L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n41793","headword_ar":"وَادٌّ","root":"wd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wid~N","text_ar":"وِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2932}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n44518","headword_ar":"وَادٍ","root":"wdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A valley; a water-course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torrent-bed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a river;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a space intervening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any such space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between mountains or hills;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through which a torrent runs forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occasionally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) for which reason it is thus called. (M, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a biwaAdiyhi","text_ar":"حَلَّ بِوَادِيهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAEai EalaY bayoEihi","text_ar":"بَاعَِ عَلَى بَيْعِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in one of the senses explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byE","text_ar":"بيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He superseded him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}